author: Inside Edition
description: Eagle-eyed CBS Mornings viewers noticed something different about Gayle King's lips. King said that she went to the dentist and had a bad reaction to anesthesia. Over on the TODAY Show, Savannah Gutherie, just revealed she will undergo vocal surgery. Gutherie says she said she has to be "totally silent" during her recovery. Meanwhile, the world's most coveted cake is the Tom Cruise Coconut Cake. He sends the white chocolate coconut bundt cake to all his A-list friends every Christmas.
title: CBS Mornings' Gayle King Answers Questions About Her Lip

author: Inside Edition
description: An angry crowd of students confronted a travel agent who they say ripped them off over a school trip. Robert Goodwin is accused of defrauding $400,000 from 104 high school students. The students had signed up for a trip to Italy and Greece, which cost $3,500. Police say a month before the students were due to leave, they received an email from Goodwin saying his travel agency was shutting down and the trip was canceled. Police say no one got a refund from the company.
title: Students Confront Travel Agent They Say Scammed Them Out Of $400K

author: Inside Edition
description: A tip led police to the killer behind the Brown University shooting and the murder of an MIT physics professor. Claudio Neves Valente, 48, took his own life inside a storage unit in Salem, New Hampshire, as authorities closed in. A Reddit post by a person identified as "John" in court papers was a big break in the case. John told police he had a confrontation with the suspect two hours before he opened fire, killing two students.
title: Suspect In Brown University And MIT Professor Shootings Found Dead

author: Inside Edition
description: The Kennedy family is up in arms Friday at the renaming of the Kennedy Center to the Trump-Kennedy Center. The signage was attached to the building Friday. It reads "The Donald  J. Trump and the John F. Kennedy Memorial for the Performing Arts." The name on the center's website also changed. One Kennedy family member is calling the move "an insult to a great president." Many questions are rising about the legality of the name change.
title: Kennedy Family Outraged Over 'Trump-Kennedy Center' Renaming

author: Inside Edition
description: A barn went up in flames with animals trapped inside. It was none other than county singer and TikTok star Taylor Holder trying to kick through the fence. In a desperate effort, he tried to save the goats, pigs, and other animals on his farm outside Nashville. He jumped the fence and passed the animals to his girlfriend, Zoey. Holder and a friend were able to bring the fire under control and within minutes the fire department arrived. Holder spoke with Inside Edition about the whole ordeal.
title: Country Singer Taylor Holder Saves Animals From Burning Barn

author: Inside Edition
description: Megyn Kelly faced a firestorm of condemnation Friday after questioning whether the defense could compare the murders of Rob and Michele Reiner to the Menendez case. Reaction on social media has been swift. Inside Edition asked famed criminal defense attorney Mark Geragos to weigh in. Geragos says the mental health issue could prevent Nick Reiner from ever standing trial. Meanwhile, a private gathering was held at the home of comedian Albert Brooks in Santa Monica on Monday night.
title: Megyn Kelly Under Fire After Comparing Reiner Murders To Menendez Case

author: Inside Edition
description: Some Walmart shoppers in Mississippi got a dangerous surprise in their baked goods. Police in Biloxi say customers found razor blades and fishing hooks in their bread and muffins purchased at several locations. Investigators say the stores combed through their bakery sections to pull potentially tainted items off the shelves. An official tells local media the first incidents were thought to be isolated. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Woman Arrested After Razor Blades, Fishing Hooks Found In Walmart Bakery Items

author: Inside Edition
description: A former sports reporter and her husband were both found dead in their Alabama home, in what police say was a murder-suicide. The bodies of Christina Chambers, 38, and Johnny Rimes, 41, were found with gunshot wounds according to the Hoover Police Department. Their 3-year-old son was also found inside the house, unharmed. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Former Alabama Sports Reporter Found Dead In Murder/Suicide: Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: A group of marathon runners held an impromptu race with a catch, staging the first backwards mile race in Antarctica! Not only did they run, walk and stumble through the whole race with their backs to the finish line, but they did it in the coldest place on earth. They were all there anyway to run the annual Antarctic Ice Marathon. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Runners Stage First Backwards Mile Race In Antarctica
